window.bookSummaryJSON = "Author of the beloved <i>Redwall</i> series, Brian Jacques is one of the most popular fantasy authors in the world, with over 40 million books in print. This <i>New York Times</i> best seller will impress listeners with its original twist on the legend of the ghost ship, the Flying Dutchman. <p> The Flying Dutchman is cursed to sail the seven seas for all eternity without rest. The two innocent castaways, a young mute boy named Neb and his dog, Denmark, are washed overboard from the hoary yacht and end up on the seashore of a cozy, yet endangered English village. With the help of the townsfolk, Neb and Denmark solve riddles and search for the buried secrets that can save the village and its people.</p> <p> A brilliant departure from the <i>Redwall</i> series, this novel will undoubtedly satisfy longtime Jacques fans and newcomers alike.</p>"; 
